  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, suffer and struggle suggest emotion; learn, guide, fool, mislead, deceive, decide, etc.",
    "imply cognitive abilities; and steer, move, tackle, etc.",
    "suggest human-like behaviors.",
    "Understand is a top verb only within the ACL dataset, connecting to Bender and Koller (2020)'s discussion of inaccurate claims in research papers about LLMs \"understanding.\"",
    "The term \"natural language understanding\" has for many decades been the standard name for components of NLP related to semantics (Allen, 1995), reflecting how this anthropomorphic metaphor has long since permeated the field's vocabulary."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The term \"natural language understanding\" has for many decades been the standard name for components of NLP related to semantics (Allen, 1995), reflecting how this anthropomorphic metaphor has long since permeated the field's vocabulary."
  ]
